node.areas_of_interest_freeform: LEADERSHIP PREVAILS.  Moonshots Capital is a seed-stage venture capital firm that invests in extraordinary leadership. Great leaders are hard to come by. We believe the best ones are military-trained or trial-by-fire entrepreneurs who have the ability to motivate others to action, inspire trust, and plan heuristically. We invest with conviction when those attributes are present. We have collectively founded and operated 14 companies, and have personally invested in more than 120 ventures.

node.areas_of_interest_freeform: Innospark lives at the intersection of decades of experience, both operating and investing, and a conviction in the outsized role that artificial intelligence will play in our future.  We invest in founders solving hard problems across business, healthcare, life science and education, partnering with them to work through challenges and build industry changing companies.  We also focus on investing for social good.

node.areas_of_interest_freeform:
FV is a venture capital syndicate that invests in early-stage technology startups charting the future in mobility, climate, robotics, proptech, security — with a technical focus on software, robotics, and artificial intelligence.

We invest and are a strategic partner for startups with exponential solutions, mission-driven founders (and a clear vision), who are superior operators, having some early evidence of traction (i.e. mvp, revenue, partnerships) in large, growing, or unlocked markets

node.person.name: Paul Anthony Claxton
node.areas_of_interest_freeform: We're interested in founders building AI products, services and systems that will be implemented into IoT and SaaS use cases. These cases can apply to dual-use, healthcare, infrastructure, mobility, cyber security, space exploration etc. The companies should be AI first, AI as a Service, or AI as a Solution, not AI powered. We invest with an ESG focus, so the companies should be satisfying some impact component of ESG. Questions to ask: Will it change the way we live? How about the way we work?
